  "description": "Demolition of the existing building and erection of a 1-bed four story\r\nresidential unit.&nbsp;",
  "decision_date": "23/05/2023",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed roof terrace and front elevation windows, by reason of location, position, proximity, to neighbouring buildings, and lack of sufficient overlooking mitigation measures, would result in a loss of privacy for neighbouring dwellings contrary to LP2 &#x27;Development and Amenity&#x27; of the Hackney local plan and D6 &#x27;Housing Quality and Standards&#x27; of the London plan as well as the guidelines Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of inadequate internal GIAs for the double bedroom, layout over five stories for a 1 bed unit, and lack of adequate daylight and sunlight for future occupants, would result in a substandard level of accommodation as a result of insufficient floorspace contrary to policy D6 (Housing Quality and Standards) of London Plan 2021 and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Local Plan 2033 and the guidance contained within the Mayor of London&#x27;s Housing SPG.&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to contribute towards the Carbon Offset Fund,&amp;nbsp; would fail to meet the London Objective of being a zero-carbon city by 2050, contrary to policies SI 2 (Minimising greenhouse gas emissions) of the London Plan (2021), policy&amp;nbsp; LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6 (Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to Policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021) and Policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its excessive height,&amp;nbsp; scale, massing, detailed design, position and location would result in an obtrusive and incompatible form of development which would fail to respect the character and appearance of the subject property and the terrace of which it forms part and would fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the Mare Street Conservation Area. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity through the Design-led Approach) and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan 2021, LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033, and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD 2009.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
